      "content": "The concept of a \"good\" nationalism is a dangerous illusion because the moment a group defines itself as superior or uniquely deserving, it sets the stage for intolerance. Any ideology that demands absolute loyalty to a singular national narrative inevitably requires the marginalization or suppression of internal dissent and minority groups. Therefore, its inherent drive toward in-group favoritism makes it fundamentally corrosive to pluralistic societies.",
